  "edge_hypothesis": "CCI crossing +100/-100 thresholds detects momentum acceleration — a fundamentally different mechanism from the dead CCI zero-cross approach. When CCI breaks above +100, buying pressure is statistically extreme and likely to continue in trending regimes. T3 (triple-smoothed EMA with volume factor 0.7) provides smoother trend confirmation than raw EMA, filtering out false CCI breakouts during chop. This targets ETH 4h where all 10 ACCEPTs live. Hypothesis: momentum breakout detection via CCI thresholds combined with adaptive trend filtering produces a distinct edge profile from the existing transition-detection and mean-reversion families.",
